reviews.author: Natalie Surin
reviews.text: Such an amazing vibe!! Step in and get a taste of the motherland. A must do when visiting Dubai. From the staff, to the bartender, to the manager. This place knows what they are doing. Made us come back more than once. Thank you! ☺️

reviews.author: Nima
reviews.text: Came here to celebrate a birthday on a Sunday night. It was not busy at all. Service was great. Food was good. The asun was very very spicy though. I really enjoyed the coleslaw. The Jollof was a bit underwhelming, but everything else was decent.

reviews.author: Haddy Banks
reviews.text: Had a great experience at Enish Dubai ! The food was really good and the ambience was cozy and welcoming. Shoutout to Yinka, our server, who was super attentive and friendly. Highly recommend!

reviews.author: TK Popoola
reviews.text:
Enish Dubai – A Taste of Authentic Nigerian Cuisine in an Upscale Setting

Enish Dubai is a true gem for lovers of authentic Nigerian cuisine. Nestled in an upscale location, the restaurant boasts a vibrant and stylish ambiance that perfectly complements the rich flavors of its menu. Whether you’re dining with friends, family, or on a special occasion, the setting is both welcoming and elegant.

From the moment we walked in, the service was impeccable. Linda, our host, was exceptional—warm, attentive, and knowledgeable about the menu. She made sure we had everything we needed and provided great recommendations.

Now, onto the highlight—the food! We indulged in a variety of traditional Nigerian dishes, and every bite was a delight. The moimoi was perfectly steamed and flavorful, the pepper soup had just the right kick, and the puff-puff was soft, sweet, and addictive. The ayamase (ofada stew) was rich and deeply spiced, while the abula was a perfect blend of amala, ewedu, and gbegiri, delivering an authentic taste of home.

Overall, Enish Dubai exceeded our expectations. Whether you’re in Dubai or visiting any of their locations worldwide, I highly recommend Enish for an unforgettable dining experience. If you love Nigerian cuisine or are eager to try something new, this is the place to be!

reviews.author: Chika Chima
reviews.text: Food was delish, our waitress Rita was phenomenal!! Matter of fact she set the tone for the experience. From our initial entrance, she greeted us warmly, sat us, and brought the menu. Next she dropped off menu and complimentary puff puff. She was very attentive, inquired if I wanted to eat with my food with fork and spoon or use my hand; made excellent recommendations on the food which was perfection!! I had Oha soup and poundo while hubby did Abula and we thoroughly enjoyed our dishes!!! Definitely a great experience and ask for Rita if she is working, you can tell she enjoys her work and has a passion for ppl.
